
# Security Policy

This repository contains an educational SHA256 password cracking demonstration intended for **authorized** and **ethical** cybersecurity research only.

The project is "as-is" and not actively maintained. 

---

## Responsible Use Notice

You may only use this code on:

- Hashes you generated yourself, **or**
- Hashes you have explicit permission to test.

Any unauthorized usage violates ethical guidelines and may violate local laws.  
The author is **not responsible** for any misuse of this tool.

---

## Scope & Limitations

- This tool is strictly for **educational and research** environments.  
- No wordlists are included to avoid licensing or misuse concerns.  
- The project is provided **as-is** and is **not actively maintained**.

---

## Reporting Vulnerabilities

If you discover a bug or a security concern **in this repository**, please report it privately:

- Open a **private GitHub security advisory**  
- https://github.com/pesohs/SHA256-Password-Cracking-Project/security/advisories  
- OR contact me via GitHub  
- https://github.com/pesohs

Please **do not** open public issues for sensitive findings.

---

## Disclosure Policy

- Please allow reasonable time for assessment and fixes before making anything public.
- Proof-of-concept details should be shared privately first.
- No guarantees of response times or ongoing maintenance are provided.

---

## Contribution Guidelines

Contributions are welcome **as long as they support responsible, ethical use**.

Examples of allowed contributions:

- Code optimization  
- Documentation improvements  
- Security best-practice suggestions  
- Testing enhancements  
- Defensive / educational content  

Examples of disallowed contributions:

- Malicious automation  
- Exploits targeting real systems  
- Bundled wordlists meant for cracking real accounts  

By responsibly using and contributing to this project, you help promote ethical cybersecurity education.

